title: SFH on HA's Independent Review Committee report
content_text:
p>
	Following is the transcript of remarks made by the Secretary for Food and 
	Health, Dr Ko Wing-man, at the Legislative Council Complex today (July 9): Secretary for Food and Health: The Hospital Authority (HA) has appointed an 
	Independent Review Committee regarding the suspension of clinical duties of 
	Professor Yu (Cheuk-man) of the cardiology unit of the Prince of Wales 
	Hospital. The HA has just released the full report of the committee. I 
	notice that in regard of the hospital chief executive's decision to suspend

notice that in regard of the hospital chief executive's decision to suspend 
	part of the clinical duties of Professor Yu, the review committee concluded 
	that it is an appropriate decision basing on patient safety. Secondly, the 
	Independent Review Committee also regarded the appointment procedure of the 
	two expert panels to be in order. However, the review committee is of the 
	view that the management of the Prince of Wales Hospital could have done 
	better in terms of communication with Professor Yu regarding the suspension 
	of part of his clinical duties. The Food and Health Bureau will study the

of part of his clinical duties. The Food and Health Bureau will study the 
	report in details and follow up with the HA. Reporter: (on Professor Yu's performance of procedures) Secretary for Food and Health: Regarding the resumption of Professor Yu's 
	clinical duties, the Independent Review Committee also recommended the HA to 
	further discuss with the Chinese University of Hong Kong (CUHK) before 
	deciding on whether to adopt the experts' recommendations. Reporter: (on what procedures Professor Yu can perform) Secretary for Food and Health: At the present moment, according to the HA,

Professor Yu can perform such procedures as cardiac catheterisation as well as cardiac pacing. As to the process and criteria for the hospital to allow Professor Yu to resume other types of procedures, it will be left for the HA to further discuss with the CUHK. (Please also refer to the Chinese portion of the transcript.)
